postcontent: This is a VERY rare S & W "K" frame model 66-4 with 3 inch barrel. This revolver has had custom work done on it at the S & W Performance Center. It has had a trigger job (very sweet smooth double action pull and around a 2 pound single action pull) It came with a beautiful satin finish, which is a little darker than stainless. It also was ported at the Perf. Center. I got this around 2000. I shot it about a dozen times then cleaned it thoroughly and put it in my safe to collect. This is a gem of a revolver, if your a revolver person or collector. It is easily in 96 to 98 % condition and maybe even better..I can not see a blemish on it. The turn rings are barely visible. Comes with plastic box and manual. I have seen these things on a gun website or two a few times and they have been well over what i'm asking for this. title: For Sale:  Daisy & Heddon .22 Cal. Rifle V/L Caseless ammunition
postcontent: Daisy & Heddon V/L .22 VL rifle. Rare .22 caliber single shot rifle that shoots caseless ammo. Excellent condition with about 400 rounds of ammo. The Daisy V/L was the first production rifle for caseless ammo.It was released in 1968 by Daisy. In 1961 Case Hough, the president of Daisy purchased the design of a new firearm system. The new system was developed by a Belgian Chemist. The V/L ammunition consisted of a .22 caliber bullet with a small cylinder of propellant on the back, and no primer. The rifle resembled a typical spring-air rifle, but the 2000° hot, high pressure air served not only to propel the projectile but also to ignite the propellant on the back of the V/L cartridge. The rifle uses a small, unique and well designed part called an Obturator (obturator/ignitor) to compress the air as it is pushed through a tiny hole. This air is heated as it is pushed through the small hole enough to ignite the powder of the caseless round. Please check my listings as I have listed or will be will be listing many guns in coming days and weeks as I get time.( Ruger Night watchman, Mini 14, Colt WWII commeratives, Gold Cup, M1911A1, Beretta 92, PX4,CX4, Calico M100, M950, Marlin 444, 45-70, 44 Mag  Para Companion 7.45, P14.45, P14, P16,P18 Limited, Taurus PT1911, 1949 Argentine Sist.
